# Explorer_Comm
Written by Joseph Dizon rbdizon@yahoo.com

Explorer_Comm is a desktop application written in Java. Its purpose is to run scripts written in Forth.
This can be useful for automating communication with a target device such as ESP32.
Communication can be done using text commands sent through serial port or HTTP request

System Requirement: Java Runtime Environment
Some knowledge of the Forth language is necessary

Download and put (or unzip) all the files in the same folder.
To start the app in Linux, execute the file "Explorer_Comm.sh".
In Windows, doubleclick the file "Explorer_Comm.jar" (assuming Java is the default for .jar files).

The upper text window is the input or script editor contains the script.
The lower text window is the output contains the result of the script.

The included "ESP32.for" is a script file written in Forth to comminicate with an ESP32 device. The ESP32 device should have uploaded the included ESP32.ino file.

Open the Forth file "ESP32.for". The script will appear in the upper window. The script can be edited in the upper window.

To run the "start" function, click the 'Run "start"' button.

To run the script starting from a specific line in the script editor, put the cursor anywhere in the line then click the button "Exec Line (F11)" or press F11.

Resources for the Forth language can be found in the internet.
